title: Grateful Dead Live at World Music Theatre on 1990-07-23

reviews.review_text:
Road Weary Performance Has Its Moments Brent's last show is more historic than anything to write mom about unless it's to ask her to send money so you can get home.

Yet, surprisingly, it does have its moments where Jerry goes off into the ionosphere and Bobby follows closely behind. Brent is also right along side providing Hornsby-like piano etchings. It must have been hot weather on that night. There seems to be an ever drifting languor parading to and fro throughout this 2 hr 20 minute expose'. 

This recording and remaster is classically refined in its definition and all the instruments and vocals are there. Phil roars passively throughout like an erupting volcano 700 miles windward. Check out the jam and space. It will set you reaching for more straws.

I awarded this a four star rating merely because the sound is so oogley-boogley and for its inherent tribute to a very fine and underrated keyboardist/singer/songwriter playing in his final show on earth.

Brent died in my home town, Lafayette, CA, three days later.

Because of Brent's affiliation with this neverending band, Brent shall never be forgotten and it is fitting that, at least, he will never fall into the category of the unremembered.

Such would be an affront to all struggling keyboardist/singer/songwriters for they all have merit, but not all have longevity. Brent has longevity.

Safe to say that Brent was one who struggled even after he didn't need to -- as opinion might merit, but we all struggle, no matter our lot or position in life and living. And there is the rub...

Ah, yes, to struggle. That is the key that unlocks the vault. That is the mettle which sharpens the iron. Oh, the great struggle!

Sharpen us.

Cleave us asunder.

Deliver us whole.

Pacify.

Mommy!

the real version of this show  - the stereo one - I'm sorry, but I meant to say that just the one out of the three here is mono.. the one that most people downloaded. I kept checking back waiting for the stereo one to pop up and when I finally found it here after many months it was too late to download.
